        <description>
          <![CDATA[<p><img src="https://www.ohio.edu/sites/default/files/2023-01/20091104-_DSC2383.jpg" style="max-width:320px;" /></p>
<p><strong>Address:</strong> 28 West Green Dr., Athens, OH 45701</p>
<p><strong>Campus Green:</strong> West Green</p>
<p><strong>Building Type:</strong> Academic</p>
<p><strong>Current Use:</strong> Stocker Engineering and Technology Center is located in the West Green, coordinates E-3 on the campus map. It is marked as #120 on the map.<br/><br/>The C. Paul and Beth K. Stocker Engineering and Technology Center houses Ohio University&#39;s Russ College of Engineering and Technology. The College&#39;s departments include Chemical Engineering, Civil Engineering, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, Industrial and Manufacturing Systems Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Airway Science, and Industrial Technology.<br/><br/>Stocker Center provides more than 3.5 acres of classroom, laboratory, lecture hall, and office space. A high-technology computing and communication network is available for transmission of voice, data, and video, linking the departments. Other features include computer-aided design and computer-aided manufacturing networks, a rooftop area for outdoor antennas and solar experiments, and energy-efficient heating and cooling systems.</p>
<p><strong>Building Directory:</strong> <a href="https://www.ohio.edu/building-directory/stocker-center">https://www.ohio.edu/building-directory/stocker-center</a></p>]]>
