<p><strong>Campus Green:</strong> West Green</p>
<p><strong>Building Type:</strong> Mixed Use</p>
<p><strong>Current Use:</strong> The Convocation Center has mixed uses for Ohio University Athletics, Academic offices and a Residence Hall.<br/><br/>Seating 13,080 people, the building houses Ohio University Bobcat basketball, volleyball, and wrestling matches; offices for Intercollegiate Athletics, including the baseball, basketball, cross country, field hockey, golf, soccer, softball, track, volleyball, and wrestling programs, and part of the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science; and hosts large events like concerts, Commencement and Convocation ceremonies, and more for the University. <br/><br/>It is also a residence hall. View the Convocation Center Residence Hall information</p>
