      <Placemark>
        <name>Galbreath Chapel</name>
        <description>
          <![CDATA[<p><img src="https://www.ohio.edu/sites/default/files/2021-07/20070822-LD4225.jpg" style="max-width:320px;" /></p>
<p><strong>Address:</strong> 43 University Terrace, Athens, OH 45701</p>
<p><strong>Campus Green:</strong> College Green</p>
<p><strong>Building Type:</strong> Mixed Use</p>
<p><strong>Current Use:</strong> Galbreath Chapel is located in the College Green, coordinates H-4 on the campus map. It is marked as #5 on the map.<br/><br/>The Helen Mauck Galbreath Memorial Chapel is a gift of alumnus John Galbreath in memory of his first wife, whom he met while they were students at the university. Campus legend holds that it marks the spot where the two first kissed.<br/><br/>The chapel is used by people of all faiths for personal prayer and meditation. It is also used for memorial services, bar mitzvah, weddings, receptions, and christenings. Cultural events such as organ concerts, musical programs, poetry readings, lectures, religious drama, liturgical dance, and exhibitions of religious art are held there. Many fraternities and sororities choose it for formal initiation ceremonies and receptions. The chapel has a seating capacity of 150. The chapel is open to the public by appointment only; see their home page for contact information.</p>
<p><strong>Building Directory:</strong> <a href="https://www.ohio.edu/building-directory/galbreath-chapel">https://www.ohio.edu/building-directory/galbreath-chapel</a></p>]]>
        </description>
