<p><strong>Building Type:</strong> Mixed Use</p>
<p><strong>Current Use:</strong> The Ohio University Observatory is sited at The Ridges on the hilltop between Konneker Research Laboratory and the water tower.<br/><br/>Astrophysical Institute faculty members sponsor programming at the observatory. It is used for both academic and recreational purposes, encouraging the learning and identification of constellations, planets, and other celestial bodies.<br/><br/>Learn more about the Ohio University Observatory</p>
